#Gui Tooltips
tooltip.colorfulmobs.selection.confirm=Confirm: When this button is clicked, the color currently set within the GUI shall be applied to the entity.
tooltip.colorfulmobs.selection.red=Red Slider: This slider controls the amount of red which is used when rendering the entities texture. Increasing this value will make the texture more red, while decreasing it will make it less red.
tooltip.colorfulmobs.selection.green=Green Slider: This slider controls the amount of green which is used when rendering the entities texture. Increasing this value will make the texture more green, while decreasing it will make it less green.
tooltip.colorfulmobs.selection.blue=Blue Slider: This slider controls the amount of blue which is used when rendering the entities texture. Increasing this value will make the texture more blue, while decreasing it will make it less blue. 
tooltip.colorfulmobs.selection.alpha=Transparency Slider: This slider allows for control over the transparency for the entities texture. Increasing this slider will make the texture more transparent, while decreasing it will make it less transparent.

